    "Summary": "The covered entity's (CE) business associate (BA) operated a server containing the electronic protected health information (ePHI) of 2,360 individuals that was vulnerable to access by unauthorized persons for over four months.  The ePHI included transcribed doctors' notes, which may have included medical diagnoses, clinical laboratory results, diagnostic imaging reports, emergency department records, and medication administration.  Upon discovery of the breach, the CE engaged a computer forensic expert to investigate the incident and terminated the BA agreement.  As a result of OCR's investigation, the CE ensured that its BA secured the server, verified that the server was no longer accessible from the Internet, and required the BA to return or destroy all of the CE's ePHI.",
